title: Grateful Dead Live at Denver Coliseum on 1973-11-20
description:
Set I
Ramble On Rose, Mexicali, Don't Ease Me In, Black-Throated Wind, Brown-Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, To Lay Me Down, The Race Is On, They Love Each Other, Me And Bobby McGee, Tennessee Jed, Big River, Row Jimmy, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow, Casey Jones
Set II
Promised Land-> Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Mississippi Half Step-> Dire Wolf, Looks Like Rain, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Truckin'-> The Other One-> Mind Left Body Jam-> Stella Blue; Sugar Magnolia; E: Uncle John's

reviews.review_text: SOLID Performance! This show, coupled with Road Trips, volume 4 is an excellent cross-section of period songs. Too bad GDM didn't have the foresight to release these two (11/20-21/73) as a set. The only real caveat is Sunshine Daydream. Bob and Donna Jean's vocal chords sound shredded.
